19 chief of police in office on the effective date of this Paragraph, unless the office is
20 vacant or filled by an officer temporarily appointed as of that date. The term of
21 office of the chief of police shall be concurrent with that of the appointing mayor and
22 aldermen. The board of aldermen, upon recommendation of the mayor, shall
23 establish the salary of the chief of police and shall, by ordinance, establish the duties,
